  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_3d00e7b28dad67d6e49e6f07a128fc11">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Banners, pennants, pillows, runners, jackets, blazers, reunion items, graduation robes and regalia, stuffed animal mascots, and other cloth items. Examples include a Cornell University doctoral hood, originally owned by Dr. William J. Edens, Ph.D. 1937 and Class of 1941 blazer owned by Arthur Townsend Klinger.</p>  </scopecontent>
